        <table id="t1602536" tblwidth="pg-wide" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Blower Motor Circuits Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.52in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.73in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.71in"/>
                <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Blower Motor Circuit Troubleshooting</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Make the following checks with ignition key OFF, the Blower Motor connector connected,
                                and the Linear Power Module connector connected.
                            </para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>When making resistance checks (for short circuits), always remove power and
                                    isolate the circuit being checked.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Blower motor</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Blower motor should not run constantly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If the blower does NOT run constantly, proceed to the next step.</para>
                            <para>If the blower runs constantly:</para>
                            <seqlist>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check for an open 1000 Ohm resistor between cavities 2 and 3 of the Linear
                                        Power Module connector. Replace if open.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>If the resistor is ok, remove BATTERY voltage from the circuit and isolate the
                                        short to ground to one of the following:
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>the harness circuit between Blower Motor connector, cavity B and Linear Power
                                        Module connector, cavity 4.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>the blower motor assembly, cavity B of its connector (when disconnected from
                                        harness).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>the linear power module, at terminal 4.</para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Blower Motor Circuit Troubleshooting (continued)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with ignition key ON, Linear Power Module connector and Blower Motor connector
                                disconnected.
                            </para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>When making resistance checks (for short circuits), always remove power and
                                    isolate the circuit being checked.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Linear Power Module Connector, cavity 1 to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 Volts dc</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing check for:</para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <title>Version 1 Circuits</title>
                                <item>
                                    <para>a blown fuse (F4) - (before replacing fuse, check for a short circuit between
                                        fused circuit and ground)
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>an open circuit between Linear Power Module Connector, cavity 1 and fuse F4
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <title>Version 2 and version 3 (Early Production) Circuits</title>
                                <item>
                                    <para>a blown fuse (F6) - (before replacing fuse, check for a short circuit between
                                        fused circuit and ground)
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>an open circuit between Linear Power Module Connector, cavity 1 and fuse F6
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <title>Version 3 (Late Production) Circuits</title>
                                <item>
                                    <para>a blown fuse (F20) - (before replacing fuse, check for a short circuit between
                                        fused circuit and ground)
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>an open circuit between Linear Power Module Connector, cavity 1 and fuse F20
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Linear Power Module connector, cavity 1 to cavity 3</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 Volts dc</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for: an open circuit between Linear Power Module
                                connector, cavity 3 and ground stud (1851).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Blower Motor connector, cavity A to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 Volts dc</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing check for: an open circuit between Blower Motor connector,
                                cavity A and fuse F4.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Linear Power Module Connector, cavity 2 to cavity 3</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>0 to 5 Volts dc (depends on setting of Blower Speed Control) - Voltage range may
                                differ slightly
                                <emph type="bold">BUT,</emph>
                                should be lowest when control is fully ccw, and should increase as the control is turned
                                cw, to its highest value when control is fully cw.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing or does not respond correctly to Blower Speed Control, check
                                for:
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>an open or shorted to ground circuit, between connector (1200), cavity A11 and
                                        cavity 2 of the Linear Power Module Connector. NOTE: There is a 1000 Ohm
                                        resistor between this circuit and ground.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>a defective HVAC Control Head</para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <note>
                                <para>If the blower motor will not stop running when the blower speed control is set to
                                    OFF, check for an open 1000 Ohm resistor
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Blower Motor Circuit Troubleshooting (continued)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Make the following checks with ignition key OFF, the Blower Motor connector,
                                connected; and the Linear Power Module connector, disconnected.
                            </para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>When making resistance checks (for short circuits), always remove power and
                                    isolate the circuit being checked.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <note>
                                <para>Connecting the indicated jumper should energize the blower. Once blower operation
                                    is checked, REMOVE jumper.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                            <para>Momentarily connect a jumper from Linear Power Module connector, cavity 4 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>The blower should energize at maximum speed while the jumper is connected.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If the blower turns on replace the linear power module.</para>
                            <para>If the blower does NOT turn on:</para>
                            <seqlist>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check for an open circuit between Blower Motor connector, cavity B and Linear
                                        Power Module connector, cavity 4.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>If the circuit checks ok, replace the blower assembly.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
